<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7278> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7278" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Since he assisted in the prosecution of Milo in 52 (Ascon. 34C), he very probably gained entrance to the Senate before 31, and, if he is the ..]# named in the SC de Mitylenaeis (IGRP 4.33; but Sherk, RDGE no. 26, col. c, 14, p. 150, reads ..]#), he was certainly there in 25. Mommsen and Münzer (RE no. 15) suggest that the senator of 25 was son of no. 299, but the order of names, though fragmentary, is in favor of an older man. (TJC)" .
